06/01/2005
NIS, Serbia-Montenegro -- The former head of the Serbia-Montenegro Army's general staff, Major General Branko Krga, said Wednesday (5 January) that there are no indications of resumed tensions in southern Serbia. 
During a visit to the Nis Army Corps with his successor, General Major Dragan Paskas, Krga said that the situation in the region is generally stable and that the federal union's military is working with KFOR personnel. 
(Danas - 06/01/05; Tanjug - 05/01/05)
